snippet.textDisplay:
Hi all old and new International Armys, and u who just wanna know more about BTS! Take your time to read this updated ”novel” by a devoted Army. I’m sure you’ll learn something new:

Part 1 of 4:
In South Korea 7-member boy band ”BTS” goes by ”Bangtan Sonyeondan”, 방탄소년단 in Korean Hangul. In English it’s roughly translated to ”Bulletproof Scoutboys”, but there isn’t an exact translation. Internationally they go by their short title BTS, sometimes adding ”Beyond The Scene”. Their group name is the reason why they officially named their fans A.R.M.Y, which also stands for Adorable Representative for Youth. In 2013, BTS explained the significant meaning behind it. Army is military in English and the body armor and military are always together, so it means that their fans will always be together with Bangtan. One of their first singles from their 2013 debute album is ”We Are Bulletproof Pt.2”.

BTS is veterans in the K-music industry. They debuted 7 years ago in June 13, 2013. Some of the members have been together for 10 years but all gathered over 8 years ago. BTS was originally planned to be a rap group since the first member was rapper RM, who since start was the best suited to be the ”leader”. Along came the other two rappers Suga and J-hope, and then Jungkook who could both sing and rap. After thinking it through they decided they wanted vocalists too. Jimin was the last member to join and had only one year as a trainee prior debute. He was a legendary top student in contemporary/modern dance in Busan Highschool of Art.
BTS really slayed their debute performance with awesome vocals and rap, impressive advanced choreo and charismatic hiphop style. They didnt look like rookies at all. Jungkook was 15 (who showcased impressive mature vocals at such young age), V and Jimin 17, leader RM 18, J-hope 19, Suga and Jin 20.
In the beginning though they faced scepticism to their ”tougher” hiphop style with alot of rap (without gloryfying drugs, demeaning women, brag about sports cars, flaunting their money etc). Even though they were teenagers their music was self-written and had ”depth and meaning”.

Besides, BTS wasn’t born with a silverspoon. They came from nothing, the tiny, poor, no-name company BigHit Entertainment, (founded by singer-songwriter/producer Bang Si-hyuk) which was near bankruptcy. Because of limited economy BTS wore cheap (but nice) clothes at their debute and had a small simple practice room. Their staff were acting in their MV’s and they didn’t even have money to rent a car and used one of their staff’s car. BTS gradually worked their way up and saved their label and in a way ”built” their own company. With BTS only, tiny BigHit was able to achieve one of the biggest groups of all time.
Despite their struggles in the beginning, the immense production work behind their MV’s is astonishing. Their MV’s high-quality are on another level. The set and engagement are like making a real movie.

With limited economy there was no lavish living. They lived together in a cheap, small, simple dorm all 7 boys cramped together sharing one toilet and shower etc. They grew up like a family and did everything together (ate, slept, showered, cooked, did the dishes, laundry, practiced, hung out). Oldest members Jin and Suga sometimes drove the youngest member Jungkook to school. He was only 13 when he joined BigHit. At their debute he was 15 and hadn’t started high school yet. In S.Korea the youngest is called maknae, and Jk got nicknamed the Golden Maknae because he was brilliant in so many things, such as winning in all kinds of sports, singing (got one of the best voices in S.Korea), dancing, rapping, drawing, painting.

Coming from a tiny company near bankruptcy which couldn’t afford big marketing campings, BTS has always been the underdogs. They’ve worked their asses off with blood, sweat and tears to get accepted, embraced and get people to listen to their music. Despite predjudice, they have today the most diversed and supportive fandom in the world. Not only young girls, but people of all ages, genders, ethnicities, nationalities, religions, backgrounds etc. They appreciate their music, constant hard work, talents as artists, performers, vocalists, rappers, dancers, songwriters, composers, producers. Their charisma and stage prescence are outstanding which is especially obvious when watching other groups perform. BTS is on another level. Moreover for just being the same normal, down-to-earth, humble, funny, charismatic, great, quite ”shy” guys with awesome personalities who on a side-note are naturally very good looking.

No matter of jet-lag, hectic schedule, tireness, stress, pressure, negativity spread about them etc, they’ve never acted or expressed themselves rudely in interviews, nor spoken badly about anyone. When performing on stage they’ve always given their all with so much passion and danced their hearts out. Despite their huge success they’ve never taken anything or anyone for granted and never will. They’ve remained the same, haven’t become stuck-up, inflated, nuts or committed ”scandals”. As RM said in his speech after winning Top duo/Group at 2019 BBMA: ”We still are the same boys since 6 years ago, we still have the same dreams, we still have the same thoughts. Let’s keep dreaming the best dreams together, thank you!”

An internationelly successful music group with 7 Korean boys singing in Korean, would never had been welcomed and accepted 20 years ago. Even though they still struggle acceptance, BTS has broken global barrieres like no other young artists have before them, both when it comes to race and language. Although they are famous worldwide, an important aspect of BTS that sets them apart from other globally big artists is that they don’t sing in English except for a few lines or words, (and one single ”Waste of me” with Steve Aoki).

They’ve broken multiple world records and has even broken their own. It’s digital album sales, physical album sales and album per-orders in this digital era, album charts, streamings on all kinds of platforms such as Soundcloud, Spotify, YT. ”Boy With Luv feat. Halsey" MV is the biggest 24 hour debute in YouTube history which made them break their own record. Moreover they’re selling out World Stadiums with the fastest sell-outs ever. Last tour 5 stadiums sold out in a single day, and tickets to Wembley sold out in 90 minutes which made BTS add more tour dates. These are stadiums that only the biggest stars got to perform at such as Michael Jackson, Paul McCartney, Madonna, Ed Sheeran etc. These have had problems even filling the arenas, definitely not selling out within 2 hours from release. Moreover these artists often need front acts, middle acts and end acts to attract more people, whereas BTS go alone.
In 2018 they were on the cover of Times Magazine, who later announced BTS as the ”Princes of pop”.

Their concert film ”Love Yourself in Seoul” which was shot on Aug. 26, 2018, at the Olympic Stadium in Seoul during their first leg of the ”BTS World Tour: Love Yourself”, had the biggest worldwide one-day box office ever for a cinema event. The film was released two months after their previous record-smashing film ”Burn The Stage”. The initial run broke One Direction’s record for the highest-grossing event cinema concert production.

In native S.Korea they’ve become national icons and ”ambassadors” for Korean popular culture. The economy has been growing because of them as they’ve contributed to an impressive large increase of tourism like no other before. BTS alone bring 3.7 billion dollars every year into the S.Korean economy. In Oct 2018 they were awarded the honorable ”Order Of Cultural Merit” by the S.Korean government and president. When they recieved their statuettes and diplomas each member was presented with their talents/skills and position in the group.
The 3 rappers are:
*RM - Main rapper, Leader of BTS, possesses incredible producing skills, made amazing contributions by placing #1 on the Billboard 200 with two consecutive albums - the first Korean artist to do so, (now it’s four #1 albums. BTS is the first since The Beatles to score three #1 albums in less than a year, and the first since The Beatles to score four #1 albums in less than 2 years.)
*Suga - Lead rapper, possesses solid rapping skills, contributes greatly to K-pop being loved by fans all over the world by showcasing incredible talents such as writing lyrics and composing songs.
*J-hope - Main dancer, in charge of the choreography of BTS, possesses excellent dancing skills, plays a large role in gathering attention to the world, completing the powerful and elaborate performances of BTS etc).
The 4 vocalists are:
*Jungkook - shown remarkable talents in all fields, including vocals, dance, songwriting and rap, contributed greatly to BTS to spreading out to the world together with Hallyu (called the Korean Wave aka Korean popular culture).
*Jimin - Lead Vocalist and Main dancer, acting as an all-around entertainer who possesses not only excellent dancing skills but also amazing vocals etc.
*Jin - Vocalist, shown multi-faceted talents through his deep emotional comprehension, unique vocals, participating in lyrics writing, leading the movement for the globalization of K-pop etc.
*V - Vocalist, singer/songwriter, charge of the killing part of the songs with his charisnatic deep voice, making great effort to spread Hallyu all over the world etc.
After recieving their medals all 7 members gave individual speeches.

I’m continuing on part 2 of 4 in the replies below. Please keep reading!
